name: Seattle: The Pink Panther and the Case of the Missing Diamond
description: This hilarious and fun Outdoor Adventure will navigate you to Seattle's hot spots, highlights and best parts of the city that we know you'll want to see. You'll discover new places, hidden gems and little nooks that you might want to return to, all while being entertained by the inimitable Inspector Clouseau, as you practice your detective skills and deduce your way to solving the Case of the Missing Diamond.

review.name: Disappointing
review.reviewBody: There is no case or puzzle to solve.  Just a series of videos with hints as to what is happening in the video.  It in no way ties to the places you are directed to visit and if you are looking for meaningful places around Seattle this is not it.  Ex.  We stopped after we were directed to an out of the way, nothing special coffee shop and then told to go to a bank.  Waste of money.

review.name: 2 Day Hiking tour of Mt Ranier and the Olympic Mountains
review.reviewBody:
Where do I begin on how bad this tour was. It came up on google as one of the top 10 tours to take. It was terrible. A mass of confusion on the meeting spot. I ended up driving 45 minutes to another spot. James the driver spoke Chinese and talked in the car only in Chinese. Didn’t explain anything in English. Left us at Mt. Ranier for 90 minutes w no view and nothing open. Did the same at Olympic Mtns but thank God it was a sunny day. Had us pay cash for park entrances but then paid w a business credit card. Seemed fishy because he charged us $45 and I think the park is $35 to get in. A lot of driving and no hiking to speak of. It was mostly people from Hong
Kong and Singapore and me the token American one day and the other day there was three of us. The hotel manager told me every American on the tour always complains how bad it is. A lot of false advertising.stopped at Safeway’s to buy lunch each day.

itemListElement.name: Best Seattle Day Hike and Snoqualmie Falls

name: Best Seattle Day Hike and Snoqualmie Falls
description:
To fully-engage in the Pacific Northwest Seattle Experience - Hiking is a must! One of the favorite pastimes of locals, the Cascade Mountain range just East of Seattle offers some of the best hiking in the world. From well-manicured trails, to sparkling Alpine Lakes, breathtaking views and of course, LOTS and LOTS of Evergreen Trees - you don't want to end your Seattle Vacation without a hike!

Unfortunately, for those unfamiliar with the area, choosing the right hike and figuring out how to get there can be an intimating task. With thousands of miles of dirt roads, and hundreds of trails to choose from, it can be overwhelming. Although rare, encounters with potentially dangerous wildlife such as Mountain Lions, Wolves, Horned Mountain Goats and Bears also happens. 

Let us take the stress out of it so you can have an enjoyable hike! We know exactly where we are going, we carry pepper spray and are trained to handle wildlife encounters and keep you safe! Have fun - hike with us!

review.name: Lot's of fun
review.reviewBody: I decided to stay the weekend in Seattle, following a business trip there. I booked this activity so that I could see Snoqualmie Falls and have the opportunity to do some hiking at the same time. My tour guide was punctual, friendly and fun to visit with while we hiked. The freshly baked muffins in the morning were an unexpected treat. The hike was fun, Snoqualmie Falls was beautiful and even the drive was scenic and enjoyable. I definitely recommend.

itemListElement.name: Private West Seattle Tour: A world away and a state of mind!

name: Private West Seattle Tour: A world away and a state of mind!
description:
West Seattle is the spit of land you can see when gazing west from downtown Seattle and Pike Place Market. It’s hard to imagine, but west Seattle has beaches and lovely little shops along the waterfront with views of Bainbridge Island and the Olympic Mountains. Home to the best record store in the city where Pearl Jam once played and one of the last stands of old growth trees in Seattle, West Seattle is a world unto itself. The city skyline view is iconic from "the west side", perfect for photos to make your friends back home wish they were with us! These are the places I bring my friends and family when they visit.

With a max of 4 people, this is a very personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores a part of the city that most visitors never see. Come explore with a 30 year local!

itemListElement.name: Private Seattle Neighborhoods 101 Tour: start building a mental map of the city!

name: Private Seattle Neighborhoods 101 Tour: start building a mental map of the city!
description: New private version of my most popular tour! Each neighborhood in Seattle has a unique feel, architectural style and social scene. Let’s take a ride and explore some of them! We will visit Capitol Hill to see some of Seattle’s beautiful old Victorian-style homes, independent funky shops, art, and our most beloved bookstore in the Pike/Pine corridor. On our way to Queen Anne we'll pass Seattle Center (home of the Space Needle and MoPOP) before heading to Kerry Park for incredible views. Then we're off to Fremont for lots of public art and charm. We'll finish at Gas Works Park for stunning views, historic preservation and a glimpse into the floating home communities. There are spectacular views all through this drive! If you’re a new resident of Seattle, or considering moving here, this is a great tour for you to start building a mental map of the city, guided by a resident of 30 years. With a max of 4 people in my SUV, this is a fun, personalized way to explore Seattle!

review.name: Most fun I have ever had on a tour!!!!!!!
review.reviewBody:
Going on this tour with Lynn was like seeing an old friend in a new city for the first time. A friend that knows where all of the interesting and out of the way places are and she wants to show them to you. She was just as passionate about showing us her city as we were excited to see it. Highlights include a fancy chocolate shop in a refurbished brewery, the Seattle conservatory and an introduction to Vietnamese cuisine. If you want something different from the regular old tours this is the one for you. The next time we come back to the city we are definitely going to see Lynn again. Thank you. 
                                           Shawn and Kristy

itemListElement.name: Private Capitol Hill Neighborhood Tour: Indie shops, history and attitude!

name: Private Capitol Hill Neighborhood Tour: Indie shops, history and attitude!
description:
Center of Seattle’s LGBTQ community for years, this neighborhood is packed with little independent shops, bars and attitude.

We will learn about the history of ‘the hill’, and visit one of Seattle’s oldest parks with great views of the Space Needle and an incredible historic glasshouse. Along the way, we will dance on Broadway with the aid of the bronze dance steps, explore a (literally) underground book store, and some great record shops. We will sample locally made ice cream made with milk from a herd of very happy Jersey cows living nearby, enjoy the best espresso in the city and see some of the most famous bars and live music venues in the city. This is a great way to plan your weekend agenda if nightlife is your thing! These are the places I take my friends and family when they visit, I'd like to share them with you.

With a max of 4 people, this is a very personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places most visitors never see. Come explore with a 30 year local!

itemListElement.name: Private Georgetown Neighborhood & Alki Beach Tour: historic, funky & beautiful!

name: Private Georgetown Neighborhood & Alki Beach Tour: historic, funky & beautiful!
description:
This tour highlights a neighborhood filled with art and historic architecture most travelers miss when they visit, and it's a very unique slice of old Seattle that still survives. It's a time machine! After we explore Georgetown, we will visit Alki Beach, a local favorite with great people watching, stunning views of Elliott Bay, Bainbridge Island and the Olympic Mountains. We may even spot a sea lion, a harbor porpoise, an eagle or an Orca on Alki, you never know. These are the places I take my friends and family when they visit, I'd like to share them with you.

With a max of 4 people, this is a very personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places most visitors never see. Come explore with a 30 year local!

itemListElement.name: Private Lake, Old Growth Trees & Beach Tour: Seattle's Beautiful Natural Spaces

name: Private Lake, Old Growth Trees & Beach Tour: Seattle's Beautiful Natural Spaces
description:
Believe it or not, there is an old growth forest in Seattle! Let’s cruise the scenic shores of Lake Washington and learn the incredible history of how it was “re-plumbed” while on our way to Seward Park where we will have fantastic views of Mt. Rainier (if the mountain is out!). This park is an incredible gem holding one of only 2 old growth stands left in the city. The trail through the old growth is flat, less than 1 mile long and it’s ‘flip-flop accessible’. After that, lets get some locally roasted coffee and head to West Seattle to explore the beaches of Elliott Bay including Alki Beach, a local favorite for incredible views. This tour is mostly on foot, so wear your comfy shoes and appropriate weather gear.

With a max of 4 people, this is a very personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places most visitors never see. These are the places I take my friends and family when they come to visit, and I'd like to share them with you too. Come explore with a 30 year local!

name: Seattle Scenic Tour
description: On this tour you will experience why Seattle came to be known as the “Emerald City”. The Scenic Seattle tour provides views of lakes, locks, mountains, and forest vistas, all without leaving Seattle's city limits.

name: Sunset Seattle Tour
description: With its combination of water, mountains, hills and city skyline, Seattle puts on quite a show as the sun sets. This live, narrated tour will take you from Alki Beach to North Seattle, providing sunset views of the city and Puget Sound that are usually only enjoyed by the locals.

name: The Museum of Flight Tour
description: Experience a sightseeing tour which tells the story of how Seattle came to be one of the most successful cities in the world. Explore The Museum of Flight at Boeing Field with its new Apollo 11 Mission exhibit. Museum admission is included.

name: Creative Painting Workshop
description:
Stretch your creative muscles with this hands on experience by taking part in composing the painting and then gain new painting skills by following along with Sari! This new style of workshop focuses on growing creativity and painting skills simultaneously! 

Appropriate for all skill levels, instructor Sari Luna has a one-on-one approach to getting painters on the fast track to unlocking and accessing their innate creativity. At the end of the class we will take time to celebrate the artwork we created and to reflect on what we learned in this session.

All supplies are included in the event price. You keep your acrylic painting at the end of the event!

itemListElement.name: PRIVATE Day Hike, Snoqualmie Falls, Dinner (All-Inclusive)

name: PRIVATE Day Hike, Snoqualmie Falls, Dinner (All-Inclusive)
description:
This ALL-INCLUSIVE, experience includes everything in our Day Hike + Snoqualmie Falls Package. The only difference is that it's PRIVATE. Ideal for the traveler who wants a more relaxing experience than with a large group. You'll have the guide all to yourself. It's also great for small groups of family and friends, public figures who want to enjoy the experience in an atmosphere free of bothersome, critical or nosy people. 

Finally, the experience is completely customize able. We can take you on one of our standard hikes or go over a list together before hand. Want to start early and do 2-3 hikes in one day? Want to visit other local attractions? We'll make it happen.*
*There is a $100.00 per hour fee for visiting additional locations or taking extra hikes. Fee will be calculated prior to our adventure and is due beforehand.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Delicious Donut Adventure & Walking Food Tour

name: Seattle Delicious Donut Adventure & Walking Food Tour
description:
We've always had a passion for donuts, but only recently did we realize just how many others do too. And when looking around, we didn't see anything that truly celebrated donuts in all their glory, hence the Underground Donut Tour was born. This tour is for anyone who truly enjoys donuts. At each location, you'll be able to try a curated sample of one of that location's best donuts. Our tours include such favorites as Top Pot Doughnuts, Dahlia Bakery and Daily Dozen Doughnuts in Pike Place Market. 

We also offer much more information about the route, the city, the stops, and more on our website, www.donuttour.com. Check it out today! 

We hope you can join us!

review.name: yum
review.reviewBody: Delicious, warm, yummy donuts. Decent walking pace, not too fast. Very interesting tour guide named Deb. Worth going on.

review.name: Seattle donut tour
review.reviewBody: Loved Athina and she was a wonderful guide for donuts and Seattle! Loved it for my sister and I walking tour was easy. Thanks

review.name: Excellent Tour & Donuts
review.reviewBody: The donuts and beignets were incredibly tasty, and I learned a lot from the knowledge Deb shared about downtown Seattle developments and Pike Place Market history.

review.name: One of the best and tastiest tours of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Deb our tour guide was friendly, fun and incredibly knowledgeable about donuts and Seattle! We enjoyed learning the history of the places we visited, the donuts we tasted, and extra Seattle history. The tour was a fun way to spend our morning and we felt we got an insider’s tour with Deb. Highly recommend this tour!

review.name: Great Experience!!!!
review.reviewBody: Debbie thanks for giving us the opportunity to visit Seattle, Seattle Public Market and to know the history of the Underground Donut Tour. From Dr. & Mrs. Rom D. De La Pena from Sedro Woolley,WA

review.name: Go nuts for donuts!
review.reviewBody: Thanks so much to Deb for showing us around town and being so knowledgeable! The love for Seattle and donuts was felt the whole tour. We hit 4 great shops, learned a lot of history along the way, and enjoyed the day seeing a part of Seattle easily by foot.

review.name: Sweet sensation for spring!
review.reviewBody: Deb gave a great thoughtful tour of the history of the area and market and the businesses. Her enthusiasm is wonderful and I learned more than I thought I could.

review.name: Absolutely worth it!
review.reviewBody:
The tour was absolutely amazing. Athena was super cool, and full of fun facts both about Seattle and about donuts. The walk wasn’t too taxing for us, and the donut/rest stops were perfectly spaced out. 

It turns out that four donuts in two hours is too much for me, so next time I’ll bring some food-storage containers, so the leftovers don’t get squished in my back pack!

All in all, 10/10, HIGHLY recommend! We’ll definitely add The Underground Donut Tour to our must-dos in other cities as well!

review.name: Amazing donut tour
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour, great tasting donuts, interesting facts about the city and an amazing tour guid Athena.  Highly recommended

review.name: Whimsical and Entertaining!
review.reviewBody: My husband and I had a wonderful time! Deb was a fabulous tour guide. She was knowledgeable and entertaining. The donut options were delightful. Great mini tour of Seattle with the perfect ending spot at the Pike Place Market. Couldn't have asked more perfect weather.

itemListElement.name: Into the Heart of the Olympic Mountains: Hurricane Hill

name: Into the Heart of the Olympic Mountains: Hurricane Hill
description:
If there is any one hike that will etch the magnificence of the Olympic Mountains and the Salish Sea into your memory forever, this is it.

Enjoy a day of adventure in the heart of the Olympic Peninsula with your private group. Includes two ferry rides, a visit to a native art gallery, and a moderate hike.

itemListElement.name: A Back Door to Mt. Rainier's Grand Park

name: A Back Door to Mt. Rainier's Grand Park
description: Most guided tours and hikes at Mt. Rainier are at Paradise or one of the other visitor centers, which can be crowded and offer little in the way of a true adventure or solitude. This hike takes advantage of a little-known back door to Grand Park, where solitude and wildlife viewing is almost guaranteed.

review.name: Fantastic experience with Andrew hiking in Mt. Rainier
review.reviewBody:
My wife and I spent a great day with Andrew on his "Backdoor to Mt. Rainier" trip.  I can't recommend this highly enough. Andrew took us off the beaten path into a part of the park we never would have experienced before.  Rather than walking with hundreds of people on the well traveled paths, we saw perhaps 8 others during our entire day.  The payoff was the most remarkably close up, WOW view of Mt. Rainier you can imagine (and we had hiked around Sunrise the day before, which we thought was awesome.)
Andrew took care of all the details, brought extra water, snacks, hats- you name it.  He is a delightful, interesting guy, and it made our hike more enjoyable to converse with him.  He also gave us insights about what we were seeing and the general area we would not have known. 
My wife and I are not avid hikers, though we like to be in nature, and have done some hiking back home.  This made it easy to experience the grandeur  of Mt. Rainier.      Also, don't be concerned about lack of lots of reviews. Andrew started his company recently after retiring from his web business.    Let him know your physical abilities and interests and he will tailor the experience for you.

name: 8K Day Hike and Snoqualmie Falls
description:
Enjoy an invigorating Day-Hike to either an Alpine Lake with crystal clear waters or Rugged Mountain top with stunning views! Following our hike, we'll proceed to a local restaurant where we will enjoy traditional American Food and beverages.

After we have finished our meal, we'll proceed to World-Famous Snoqualmie Falls. Learn the Historical Value this place held for Indigenous Native Americans and the the significance which it continues to play to this day.

itemListElement.name: Downtown Seattle Full-Day Trip with Daily Chauffeur

name: Downtown Seattle Full-Day Trip with Daily Chauffeur
description:
Chartering a car makes the trip flexible and comfortable, and the route can be tailored to your interests. Start from the quaint campus of the University of Washington, then experience the lively stalls and fresh seafood at Pike Place Market. Visit the Space Needle and overlook the beautiful scenery of the entire city. The colorful artworks of Chihuly Garden and Glass seem to bring us into a dream. Carey Park is full of greenery, and we relax on the grass and enjoy the gifts of nature. Finally, the modern architectural design of the Seattle Public Library is amazing, perfectly combining knowledge and beauty. Experienced drivers will also provide practical local advice to make your trip more fulfilling and enjoyable.

Recommended route: University of Washington-Pike Place Market-Space Needle-Chihuly Garden and Glass-Carey Park-Seattle Public Library

itemListElement.name: Bald Eagles Nesting Area Tour at Skagit River

name: Bald Eagles Nesting Area Tour at Skagit River
description:
We will be watching bald eagles nesting and flying above the beautiful Skagit River in Cascade Mountain Range. From the viewing areas along the river between Rockport and Newhalem we will be able to spot the bald eagles in their nests and see them in action hunting fish, birds, and animals. We will also learn about the bald eagles at the Skagit River Bald Eagle Interpretive Center in Rockport and we will see some beautiful waterfalls and pools in Newhalem and Diablo Lake in the North Cascade National Park.
On the drive to and from Seattle we will see beautiful forests and mountains. We will visit the logging town of Arlington and drive through the Suak Suiattle Indian Tribe Reservation near the old town of Darrington.

itemListElement.name: Christmas Lights and Snowflake Lane photo tour

name: Christmas Lights and Snowflake Lane photo tour
description: This Christmas tour is unique in that it takes you to some of the most special and festive holiday highlights in Seattle area. The Christmas lights in the botanical garden are beautiful and the Snowflake Lane holiday parade on Bellevue Square is one of a kind.

itemListElement.name: Small Group Seattle Full Day Tour W/ All Major Attractions

name: Small Group Seattle Full Day Tour W/ All Major Attractions
description:
Seattle is a city located in the Pacific Northwest region of the United States, in the state of Washington. It is the largest city in the state, and the 18th largest city in the country with a population of 750,000.
Seattle is known for its picturesque location, situated between the Puget Sound and Lake Washington, as well as its mild climate and frequent rainfall. The city is also famous for its coffee culture, with the birthplace of Starbucks located in Pike Place Market.
Other notable landmarks and attractions in Seattle include the Space Needle, a futuristic tower built for the 1962 World's Fair, the Museum of Pop Culture, the Seattle Art Museum, and the historic Pioneer Square neighborhood. Seattle is also home to several major technology companies, including Amazon, Microsoft, and Boeing.

review.name: Great Tour
review.reviewBody: Chris was a great tour guide. Very knowledgeable and attentive. Great tour! When we come back, we will ask for Chris……..

review.name: Great tour with Chris
review.reviewBody: Today Chris was our tour guide for our downtown Seattle tour. The content of today's visit was very detail. His bilingual explanation was great. Especially in the Museum of flight, he was very professional, patient, and detailed. He walked us through the museum and gave us important highlights. He thought of all the attractions for guests to stop and visit, so that we could enjoy both the scenery and the food. He is responsible, warm and hospitable, and reflects the high quality of a professional tour guide! Thank you again, Chris! Our family made wonderful memories in Seattle!

review.name: Wonderful trip
review.reviewBody: Chris is a very good tour guide. He is very nice, patient and has good arrangement. We enjoyed the beautiful views and have a wonderful trip.

review.name: Amazing tour guide and beautiful views
review.reviewBody: We had a great time touring Seattle. Our tour guide Duan was amazing at showing my family and I around. I would highly recomend booking a tour with him!

review.name: City tour
review.reviewBody: Our driver/guide Chris has provided excellent service. He is responsible, meticulous, and professional.  We have enjoyed this one day tour very much and want to expresss our appreciation to Chris.

review.name: Great trip
review.reviewBody: The one-day city tour is great. The Parker market, space needle tower, gas tower, museum of flight with others are all included. Thanks to our guide Chris for his good knowledge and kind advice to addressing the needs of the group.

review.name: just awful (with extra charges)
review.reviewBody: This was a bad experience for my family. The host either didn't know or didn't care to share hardly anything about the city or the places we visited. She was not very friendly or talkative. There were also misleading and hidden charges. Different guests on the tour seemed to have paid for different things. At each site she had to figure out who had paid for what. At multiple stops, guests were informed that they would have to pay for entry or wait in the lobby for 30 minutes to two hours while the rest of the group went in. We (and others) ended up paying for events that we were not interested in and not told about beforehand, but we paid so we wouldn't have to sit and twiddle our thumbs for hours. We would not do this tour again.

review.name: A sunny day in Seattle ☀️
review.reviewBody: Thanks to our guide Stella for her warm personality, her good knowledge and for her flexibility to suit the interests and needs of the group. I really enjoyed the day!

review.name: Good trip
review.reviewBody: If you wanna see the best of Seattle, this is what you wanna do! The tour was a great experience. The tour guide shared a lot of histories and information that you wouldn’t know just by going on your own. I am very glad I did this. Highly recommended!!!

itemListElement.name: Transportation to Snoqualmie Summit for Skiing, Snowboarding or Tubing

name: Transportation to Snoqualmie Summit for Skiing, Snowboarding or Tubing
description:
Have a view of the scenic Snoqualmie Falls and drive through the historic town of Snoqualmie on your way to the Snoqualmie Summit where you can go skiing, snowboarding, snowshoeing, or snow tubing - just about one hour drive east of Seattle. The beautiful snow terrain is suitable for both inexperienced and experienced people and you can rent equipment and buy lift tickets at the Summit Central where I will drop you off and direct you to those facilities. 
I will provide transportation back and forth from downtown Seattle.

name: The Loupe Lounge
description: The Loupe Lounge will be closed for the season starting April 29, and returning this Fall. Keep your eyes on our social channels and the website for more information. We look forward to welcoming you back soon. Indulge in an exclusive culinary experience in the iconic Space Needle upon the world’s 1st and only revolving glass floor, 500 feet above Seattle. Limited edition menus feature show-stopping mixology paired with locally influenced food Towers to bring your night out to new heights. Your prepaid reservation includes VIP entry, a preselected multi-course culinary Tower, three craft cocktails (additional drinks and sides available for purchase) and dessert.

itemListElement.name: Tulips and Trucks Full Day Tour

name: Tulips and Trucks Full Day Tour
description:
Visit two tulip farms on this seasonal tour, and PACCAR Technical Facility.  This is a full day tour, from approximately 8:00am to 6:00pm.

Pickup locations include downtown Seattle, Northgate, and Auburn Park and Ride at I-5 and S 272nd St.  You'll have one hour each at two different farms at the Tulip Festival, plus three hours at the truck facility.  Granola bar, fruit, and cheese provided, and bottled water.  Lunch is on your own and there are a few options. There is no restaurant stop on this tour.

itemListElement.name: Private Sunset Cruise on Lake Union

name: Private Sunset Cruise on Lake Union
description:
Please submit a reservation request for this experience as far in advance as possible as we staff based on reservations! We have 3 boats that can accommodate up to 6 guests each. Shorter and more economical tours are available in our listings "One Hour Sightseeing Cocktail Cruise", "Seattle's Favorite Sightseeing Cruise", and "Puget Sound Sailing Adventure."
Cruise in the lap of luxury aboard ‘Candére’ during a 3-hour sunset tour on Lake Union. Glide past floating homes and get a good look at Seattle-area highlights including the Space Needle, Gas Works Park, Husky Stadium, and — on a clear day — Mt. Rainier to the south of Lake Washington. With a cocktail in hand, you'll pass by drawbridges, seaplanes, and locals enjoying the lake by kayak while the sun sets.

review.name: Wonderful experience on Union Lake
review.reviewBody: We took a private two hour cruise on Union Lake, with Genevieve as our captain.  We had an absolutely delightful time.  Union Lake is fascinating place.  Genevieve is a wonderful guide who lives on the lake and can share information and history as only a true local can do.  We recommend this tour enthusiastically.

review.name: Great introduction to Seattle!
review.reviewBody: We booked this for our first afternoon in Seattle, The weather was beautiful and it was a great way to see parts of the city. Great customer service and easy to find! Highly recommend!

review.name: Great Day for All!
review.reviewBody: Did a 2 hour cruise on Lake Union yesterday with 4 other family members which was really great!  Captain Benjamin made everyone feel at ease and assigned each of us a safety related task.  Our goal was to spread my father's ashes behind my mother's girlhood home above Portage Bay and the cruise was a perfect venue for a combination of sightseeing and reflection.  The constant activity with the float planes and other boats keeps you entertained indefinitely! Would definitely recommend this cruise for close up look at lake front life!

review.name: AMAZING !!
review.reviewBody: the cruise I took was really amazing, especially with the sunset and the nice weather in our cruise day. Captain Dylan was our lead in this cruise, he was very nice, kind, and welcoming. he was very knowledgable of the area and the history of it where he was telling us some interesting stories from back then. My family and I really enjoyed it, even though we got some motion sickness LOL. I think I will take this cruise again for my next visit.

name: Blake Island Adventure
description: Your journey begins at the picturesque Bell Harbor Marina, conveniently located along Seattle’s waterfront. As you board the vessel operated by Candere Cruising, you’ll be greeted by friendly staff who will ensure your comfort and safety throughout the voyage. You’ll embark on a scenic cruise through the waters of Puget Sound. Enjoy panoramic views of Seattle’s iconic skyline, the rugged coastline, and on a clear day, stunning views of Mt Rainier. After a leisurely cruise of approximately one hour, you’ll arrive at Blake Island, a tranquil oasis steeped in Native American heritage. Blake Island offers a wealth of outdoor activities for visitors to enjoy. You can explore the island’s lush forests on nature walks, where you’ll encounter ancient cedar trees, and breathtaking views overlooking the sound. Alternatively, you can relax on the sandy beaches, and go beachcombing for shells and driftwood. After a day of exploration and discovery, you’ll reluctantly bid farewell to Blake Island.

review.name: Skyline and Seal Pups
review.reviewBody: My wife and I had a great time on The Sound with Captain Russ! He was knowledgeable and friendly. He took us to see the downtown skyline and also too see the seal pups, 12/10 had an awesome time!

review.name: A delightful cruise for both locals and tourists!
review.reviewBody: My family and I had an absolutely wonderful time on Lake Union and Lake Washington with Candere Cruising. Captain Dylan was great. His charter was the perfect blend of sightseeing, cruising, fun history facts, and plenty of great drinks for our group of 6 (a mix of local Seattleites and out-of-town visitors). We would book again in a heartbeat!

review.name: A wonderful time with a fun captain and beautiful boat
review.reviewBody: We went on a Monday afternoon with Captain Mark aboard Annie and had the best time ever! Mark was friendly, informative, and also gave us time to ourselves. He answered our questions and was attentive with our drinks - and took great pictures of us with views of downtown in the background! My husband and I took this cruise alone and it was one of the most fun things we have done in Seattle over 20 years of visiting. We saw seaplanes take off and land, geese follow our boat, and waved at the various rowing teams going by, and that doesn't even mention all of the city sights we saw. I cannot recommend them enough, it was probably my favorite thing I've ever done in Seattle and that says a lot.

review.name: Captain Maddy the Mervelous
review.reviewBody: Captain Maddy was fantastic! She knew so much about the sites we passed. She was also alert to others in the water and safely charted the water for a pleasant expereinece.  Highly recommend her and Canere Cruising!

review.name: Fantastic tour for locals and tourists - great value and so much fun!
review.reviewBody:
We took the two hour Lake Union/Lake Washington private tour. It was fantastic. The boat is nice with a table in the back that can be either shaded or unshaded. They have a full bar and start the group off with a complimentary cocktail. They take credit cards for the bar tab. 
The staff is incredibly nice. Amy was our captain and was very friendly and attentive. We’re locals and lived a nice day out on the lake. It would be a great way to show off Seattle to guests visiting. We will definitely be doing this regularly!

review.name: Lake Union Boat Tour
review.reviewBody: We really enjoyed our private 2-hour trip around Lake Union.   Mark was an excellent captain and guide

review.name: We had a great trip on Seattles Favorite Cruise
review.reviewBody:
Our captain was excellent!  I mean excellent!  She knew history, interesting current information, is a great conversationalist and above all, provided a wonderful experience for my wife and myself.

I am a native (now no longer living there) of the Sea Tac area and had never taken this cruise before.  So glad I did and would recommend it to any and all.

name: Underground Donut Tour

Savor classic donut styles like glazed, chocolate, and many others
Explore four of the top donut shops near the Monorail, Belltown, and Pike Place Market
Celebrate all things donut with like-minded donut aficionados
Enjoy this unique way of celebrating Seattle's food culture

Enjoy a local guide through Pike Place Market

Enjoy 7 tasting which add up to the perfect light meal

review.name: Bob’s Incredible!
review.reviewBody: We had a great time and learned a lot of history, and of course tasted a lot of things.  I would highly recommend this to everyone.  It shows you just enough to get you hooked.  There is so much to do here.  Bob Williams was great— very knowledgeable!

itemListElement.name: Up to 14 Guests Private Skagit Valley Tulip Festival & Deception Pass Hike

name: Up to 14 Guests Private Skagit Valley Tulip Festival & Deception Pass Hike
description:
This full day private tour brings you two great highlights of the Northwest Washington: the Skagit Valley Tulip Festival and a hike through Deception Pass, Washington's most popular state park.  Our tour includes a morning at the world famous Tulip Festival, a stop in gorgeous seaside town of La Conner for lunch, and an afternoon hike through dramatic Deception Pass State Park. 

Throughout the month of April, the Skagit Valley celebrates the coming of spring with the annual Tulip Festival.  Deception Pass is situated between Whidbey and Fidalgo Islands, boasts stunning seaside views, dense old growth forests hugged up against cliffs plunging into the water below and mesmerizing tides that flow and churn like a river between the islands. After our hike, we’ll finish off this unforgettable day with a visit to one of the Skagit Valley’s award-winning wineries for a full complimentary tasting flight.

review.name: Randonner en altitude sans forcer
review.reviewBody:
Une randonnée presque "plate" entre 2100 et 2200 m d'altitude !
Attention toutefois en cas de brouillard il est facile de se perdre car les chemins des vaches sont souvent mieux marqués que la piste. Elle est fléchée avec des marques jaunes mais en cas de brouillard épais on ne voit plus les marques.
En cas de risque de brumes à venir il vaut mieux avoir un bon GPS qui marche sans internet.
Nous nous étions perdus en septembre 2022
.
